{"id":157,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":157,"title":"Barbarian","subtitle":"","short_title":"Barbarian","uri":"/scriptures/bd/barbarian","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/barbarian.t1","order":".000.435"},[".title","Barbarian"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/barbarian.p1","order":".000.436"},"Literally means a “foreigner.” The word",["i","barbarian"],"is not used in the Old Testament but is synonymous with such words as",["i","stranger, alien, sojourner,"],"and",["i","Gentile."],"In the New Testament it connotes peoples of the Mediterranean area who are not of the Greco-Roman culture (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/1.14"},"Rom. 1:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/col/3.11"},"Col. 3:11"],") or those whose language is not familiar to the hearer, as in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/14.11"},"1 Cor. 14:11"],". See also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/28.2"},"Acts 28:2"],"."]]],"refs":null}
